            }
          ],
          "outputs": [
            {
              "id": "out_0",
              "label": "out_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# LNA (Low Noise Amplifier) — adds receiver thermal noise to the raw echo.\n# Physically the LNA is the front-end stage whose noise figure dominates the\n# receiver noise (Friis), so thermal noise is injected here, right after the\n# antenna/echo. No gain is modelled (the echo path models no attenuation yet),\n# so this stage only ADDS noise; with noise off it is a pass-through.\n#\n# SNR is defined on AVERAGE POWER (physically correct), not peak amplitude:\n#   noise_power = signal_power / 10^(SNR_dB/10),  signal_power = mean(|s_raw|^2)\n#   sigma = sqrt(noise_power)  (complex-noise mean power E[|n|^2] = sigma^2)\n# Peak-based SNR (the old sar-visualizer convention) made the injected noise\n# depend on the echo's peak, which differs wildly between a few point targets\n# and a 10^5-scatterer image (whose random-phase sum spikes the peak). Average\n# power gives a consistent SNR across target types, so focusing improves SNR the\n# same way for both. snr_db = -noise_level_db (slider shows noise level: right =\n# more noise). Deterministic via a fixed seed.\nNOISE_SEED = 1\nsnr_db = -float(noise_level_db)            # slider is noise level; SNR is its negation\nsig_power = float(np.mean(np.abs(s_raw) ** 2))   # average signal power\nif sig_power > 0:\n    noise_power = sig_power / (10.0 ** (snr_db / 10.0))   # power ratio uses /10\n    sigma = float(np.sqrt(noise_power))                  # complex-noise std (E[|n|^2]=sigma^2)\n    sig_comp = sigma / np.sqrt(2.0)                      # per-I/Q std\n    rng = np.random.RandomState(int(NOISE_SEED) & 0xFFFFFFFF)\n    noise = (rng.standard_normal(s_raw.shape) + 1j * rng.standard_normal(s_raw.shape)).astype(np.complex64)\n    s_raw = (s_raw + (sig_comp * noise).astype(np.complex64)).astype(np.complex64)\n    print('LNA: noise_level=%.0f dB (SNR=%.0f dB, avg-power)  sigma=%.3g  sig_pwr=%.3g  peak=%.3g'\n          % (noise_level_db, snr_db, sigma, sig_power, float(np.abs(s_raw).max())))\nelse:\n    print('LNA: signal power=0, no signal -> noise skipped')\n",
            "label": "LNA",
            "spec": "Low Noise Amplifier (receiver front-end). Adds receiver thermal noise to the raw echo here because the LNA's noise figure dominates the system noise (Friis). Noise model matches sar-visualizer: circular complex Gaussian, sigma = peak / 10^(SNR_dB/20), split sigma/sqrt(2) per I/Q. The slider sets noise level (= -SNR_dB); at the -60 dB minimum noise is ~1/1000 of the peak (effectively off). Gain = 1 (no amplification): the echo path models no attenuation yet, so this stage only adds noise and otherwise passes the signal through."
          },
          "codeCollapsed": true
        }
      },
