          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# === Reflection Coefficients (NUFFT) — Common stage for all FPGA routes ===\n# Self-contained NUFFT forward model. Builds frequency-domain reflection\n# coefficients S_all (Na,Nr) complex64 from POINT targets or an IMAGE target\n# (2D reflectivity), using finufft type-1. Uses GPU cufinufft when available\n# (no GPU<->CPU transfer, no CPU spreading); falls back to parallel CPU\n# finufft otherwise.\n#\n# This node STOPS at coefficient generation — it does NOT compute s_raw.\n# The downstream \"FPGA Route X\" nodes (Float / Fixed / FPGA-Save / FPGA-Load)\n# consume S_all + chirp_fft (+ fir_coefficients) and produce s_raw.\n#\n# Variables left in the kernel namespace for the route nodes:\n#   S_all            (Na, Nr) complex64  — frequency-domain reflection coeffs\n#   chirp_fft        (Nr,)    complex64  — fft(ref_chirp), NOT conjugated\n#   fir_coefficients (Na, Nr) complex64  — time-domain FIR taps per pulse\n#                                          = ifftshift(ifft(S_all, axis=1))\n#                                          (same form as the FPGA Notebook)\nimport numpy as np\nimport finufft               # CPU fallback\nimport cupy as cp           # MUST import before cufinufft: cupy registers the\n                            # CUDA runtime DLL directory (os.add_dll_directory),\n                            # without which cufinufft's native lib fails to load\n                            # (\"Could not find cufinufft library in system path\").\ntry:\n    import cufinufft         # GPU NUFFT (type-1). ~194s -> ~70s when present.\n    _HAVE_CUFINUFFT = True\nexcept Exception as _e:\n    _HAVE_CUFINUFFT = False\n    _CUFINUFFT_ERR = repr(_e)\nimport concurrent.futures\nimport time as _time\n\nNUFFT_EPS = 1e-6      # accuracy floor (~120 dB). Lower to 1e-9 for higher.\nN_WORKERS = 8         # outer parallelism; finufft inner nthreads=1\n_t0 = _time.monotonic()\n\n# ---- 0. Self-contained clutter helper (was defined in the removed n7) ----\ndef make_clutter_scatterers(count, rcs_db, half_az_m, half_range_m, seed, R0):\n    rnd = make_rand(seed)\n    sigma = (10.0 ** (rcs_db / 20.0)) / np.sqrt(2.0)\n    out = []\n    for i in range(int(count)):\n        az_m = (rnd() * 2 - 1) * half_az_m\n        sr_m = R0 + (rnd() * 2 - 1) * half_range_m\n        u1 = max(rnd(), 1e-12); u2 = rnd()\n        mag = sigma * np.sqrt(-2.0 * np.log(u1))\n        out.append(('clutter%d' % i, az_m, sr_m, mag * np.cos(2*np.pi*u2), mag * np.sin(2*np.pi*u2)))\n    return out\n\n# ---- 1. Build the source list: point targets, clutter, OR an image ----\n_mode = str(globals().get('target_mode', 'point')).strip().lower()\nTARGET_SEED  = 42\nCLUTTER_SEED = 2\nhalf = float(view_scale)\n\nif _mode == 'image':\n    from PIL import Image\n    _path = str(globals().get('image_path', '')).strip()\n    if not _path:\n        raise ValueError(\"target_mode='image' but image_path is empty — pick a file in the Image File block\")\n    _invert = str(globals().get('invert_image', 'true')).strip().lower() in ('1', 'true', 'on', 'yes')\n    _img = Image.open(_path).convert('L')\n    _gray = np.asarray(_img, dtype=np.float32)\n    if _invert:\n        _gray = 255.0 - _gray\n    _rscale = float(globals().get('range_scale', 1.0))\n    _sp_rg = (c / (2 * B)) * _rscale\n    _sp_az = La / 2.0\n    _H, _W = _gray.shape\n    _cell_rg = c / (2 * Fs)\n    _max_cols = int(np.floor(Nr * _cell_rg / max(_sp_rg, 1e-12)))\n    _az_span = float(az_pos.max() - az_pos.min())\n    _max_rows = int(np.floor(_az_span / _sp_az)) + 1\n    _cropped = False\n    if _W > _max_cols:\n        print('!! IMAGE TOO WIDE (range): %d px * range_scale %.2f > Nr %d. Cropping range to %d px (top-left). Lower range_scale or raise Nr to see it all.' % (_W, _rscale, Nr, _max_cols))\n        _gray = _gray[:, :_max_cols]; _cropped = True\n    if _H > _max_rows:\n        print('!! IMAGE TOO TALL (azimuth): %d px > az grid %d px. Cropping azimuth to %d px (top-left).' % (_H, _max_rows, _max_rows))\n        _gray = _gray[:_max_rows, :]; _cropped = True\n    _H, _W = _gray.shape\n    _rows, _cols = np.where(_gray > 0)\n    if len(_rows) == 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"image has no non-zero pixels after invert=%s / crop\" % _invert)\n    az_arr = (_rows - _H / 2.0) * _sp_az\n    sr_arr = R0 + (_cols - _W / 2.0) * _sp_rg\n    amp_arr = (_gray[_rows, _cols] / 255.0).astype(np.float64)\n    src_az = az_arr.astype(np.float64)\n    src_sr = sr_arr.astype(np.float64)\n    src_re = amp_arr\n    src_im = np.zeros_like(amp_arr)\n    NT = len(src_az)\n    print('IMAGE target: %s  %dx%d  %d scatterers (invert=%s)  spacing %.2f x %.2f m  window +/-%.0f m'\n          % (_path.split('/')[-1].split('\\\\')[-1], _H, _W, NT, _invert, _sp_rg, _sp_az, half))\nelse:\n    sources = [(n, a, s, 1.0, 0.0) for (n, a, s) in\n               make_point_targets(n_targets, half, half, TARGET_SEED, R0)]\n    n_clutter = int(clutter_n)\n    if n_clutter > 0:\n        sources += make_clutter_scatterers(n_clutter, clutter_rcs_db, half, half, CLUTTER_SEED, R0)\n    src_az = np.array([s[1] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    src_sr = np.array([s[2] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    src_re = np.array([s[3] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    src_im = np.array([s[4] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    NT = len(sources)\n    print('POINT sources: %d point + %d clutter  window=+/-%.0f m' % (n_targets, n_clutter, half))\n\n# ---- 2. Forward chirp spectrum: fft(ref_chirp), NOT conjugated, NO ifftshift ----\nchirp_fft = np.fft.fft(ref_chirp).astype(np.complex64)\n\n# ---- 3. GPU precompute weights + NUFFT coords; CPU parallel finufft ----\naz_t = cp.asarray(src_az, dtype=cp.float64)\nsr_t = cp.asarray(src_sr, dtype=cp.float64)\nrefl = cp.asarray((src_re + 1j * src_im).astype(np.complex64), dtype=cp.complex64)\naz_g = cp.asarray(az_pos, dtype=cp.float64)\nt_r_center = float(2 * R0 / c)\ninv_lam = 1.0 / float(lam)\n\n_xb_chk = -2.0 * np.pi * Fs * (2.0 * src_sr / c - t_r_center) / Nr\n_xb_max = float(np.abs(_xb_chk).max())\nif _xb_max > np.pi:\n    _fold_pct = 100.0 * float((np.abs(_xb_chk) > np.pi).mean())\n    _ext_cells = (src_sr.max() - src_sr.min()) / (c / (2 * Fs))\n    print((\"!! NUFFT FOLD WARNING: x_b reaches %.2f*pi (>1). %.0f%% of scatterers \"\n           \"fold (alias) -> spurious range banding. Image range extent = %.0f cells \"\n           \"but grid Nr = %d. Fix: lower range_scale, use a smaller image, or raise \"\n           \"Nr. Result is NOT physically correct.\") % (_xb_max/np.pi, _fold_pct, _ext_cells, Nr))\n\n\nS_all = np.zeros((Na, Nr), dtype=np.complex64)\n\nif _HAVE_CUFINUFFT:\n    gpu_pb = max(4, min(512, int(2e9 / max(1, NT) / 32)))\n    print('GPU NUFFT (cufinufft): gpu_pb=%d  n_batches=%d  NT=%d' % (gpu_pb, (Na+gpu_pb-1)//gpu_pb, NT))\n    _cuplan = cufinufft.Plan(1, (Nr,), eps=NUFFT_EPS, isign=1, dtype='complex64')\n    S_gpu_acc = cp.empty((Na, Nr), dtype=cp.complex64)\n    for pstart in range(0, Na, gpu_pb):\n        pend = min(pstart + gpu_pb, Na)\n        azb = az_g[pstart:pend]\n        daz = azb[:, None] - az_t[None, :]\n        R_eta = cp.sqrt(sr_t[None, :]**2 + daz**2)\n        squint = cp.arctan2(daz, sr_t[None, :])\n        pat = cp.sinc(squint / theta_az) ** 2\n        tau = 2.0 * R_eta / c\n        x_b = (-2.0 * np.pi * Fs * (tau - t_r_center) / Nr).astype(cp.float32)\n        carrier = cp.exp(-4j * np.pi * R_eta * inv_lam).astype(cp.complex64)\n        w_b = (refl[None, :] * pat.astype(cp.complex64) * carrier).astype(cp.complex64)\n        del daz, R_eta, squint, pat, tau, carrier\n        for i in range(pend - pstart):\n            _cuplan.setpts(cp.ascontiguousarray(x_b[i]))\n            S_gpu_acc[pstart + i] = cp.fft.ifftshift(_cuplan.execute(cp.ascontiguousarray(w_b[i])))\n        del x_b, w_b\n        cp.get_default_memory_pool().free_all_blocks()\n        print('\\r  pulses %d/%d (%.0f%%)' % (pend, Na, 100*pend/Na), end='')\n    S_all = cp.asnumpy(S_gpu_acc)\n    del S_gpu_acc\n    cp.get_default_memory_pool().free_all_blocks()\nelse:\n    print('GPU cufinufft unavailable (%s) -> CPU finufft fallback' % _CUFINUFFT_ERR)\n    gpu_pb = max(4, min(512, int(2e9 / max(1, NT) / 32)))\n\n    def _nufft_chunk(x_chunk, w_chunk, row_start):\n        plan = finufft.Plan(1, (Nr,), eps=NUFFT_EPS, isign=1,\n                            dtype='complex64', nthreads=1)\n        out = np.empty((len(x_chunk), Nr), dtype=np.complex64)\n        for i in range(len(x_chunk)):\n            plan.setpts(x_chunk[i])\n            out[i] = np.fft.ifftshift(plan.execute(w_chunk[i]))\n        return row_start, out\n\n    for pstart in range(0, Na, gpu_pb):\n        pend = min(pstart + gpu_pb, Na)\n        azb = az_g[pstart:pend]\n        daz = azb[:, None] - az_t[None, :]\n        R_eta = cp.sqrt(sr_t[None, :]**2 + daz**2)\n        squint = cp.arctan2(daz, sr_t[None, :])\n        pat = cp.sinc(squint / theta_az) ** 2\n        tau = 2.0 * R_eta / c\n        x_b = cp.asnumpy((-2.0 * np.pi * Fs * (tau - t_r_center) / Nr).astype(cp.float32))\n        carrier = cp.exp(-4j * np.pi * R_eta * inv_lam).astype(cp.complex64)\n        w_b = cp.asnumpy((refl[None, :] * pat.astype(cp.complex64) * carrier).astype(cp.complex64))\n        del daz, R_eta, squint, pat, tau, carrier\n        cp.get_default_memory_pool().free_all_blocks()\n        nb = pend - pstart\n        sub = max(1, nb // N_WORKERS)\n        chunks = [(x_b[i:i+sub], w_b[i:i+sub], i) for i in range(0, nb, sub)]\n        with concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=N_WORKERS) as ex:\n            for fut in concurrent.futures.as_completed(\n                    [ex.submit(_nufft_chunk, xc, wc, st) for xc, wc, st in chunks]):\n                st, res = fut.result()\n                S_all[pstart + st: pstart + st + len(res)] = res\n        print('\\r  pulses %d/%d (%.0f%%)' % (pend, Na, 100*pend/Na), end='')\n\n# ---- 4. Time-domain FIR taps for FPGA / Route B (fixed-point) ----\n# fir_coefficients[i, :] = ifft(S_all[i, :])  — NO fftshift.\n# Why no shift: Route B simulates FPGA's FFT-multiply-IFFT path, so\n# fft(fir_coefficients) must equal S_all exactly. A fftshift would inject\n# a (-1)^k factor in frequency domain and Route B's s_raw would be circularly\n# shifted by Nr/2 relative to Route A. Route C-out (.mat save) saves this\n# unshifted form; external HDL viewers can fftshift on display if desired.\nfir_coefficients = np.fft.ifft(S_all, axis=1).astype(np.complex64)\n\nprint('\\nNUFFT coeffs ready: mode=%s S_all=%s chirp_fft=%s fir_coeffs=%s NT=%d  (%.2fs)'\n      % (_mode, S_all.shape, chirp_fft.shape, fir_coefficients.shape, NT, _time.monotonic() - _t0))\n",
            "label": "Reflection Coefficients (NUFFT, common)",
            "spec": "【共通ステージ】NUFFTで反射係数を生成するだけのノード。s_raw は計算しない。\n\n出力（kernel namespace 経由で下流の FPGA ルートノードへ）:\n- S_all (Na, Nr) complex64  — 周波数領域反射係数（NUFFT 直出力）\n- chirp_fft (Nr,) complex64 — fft(ref_chirp)、共役なし・ifftshift なし\n- fir_coefficients (Na, Nr) complex64 — 時間領域FIRタップ = ifftshift(ifft(S_all, axis=1))。FPGA Notebook（target_sim_FFT_FPGA_convert2Image2_375M.ipynb）と同じ形式\n\n3つのFPGAルート（Float / Fixed-point / 外部FPGA）はすべてこのノードの出力を共有する。下記ルートノードのいずれかを Enabled にして s_raw を生成する:\n- n32_Float       : Route A — 浮動小数点理想 IFFT（デフォルト Enabled）\n- n32_Fixed       : Route B — fxpmath 固定小数点（3ステージ Q-format）\n- n32_FPGA_Save   : Route C-out — 係数を .mat に書き出し（HDL シミュ用）\n- n32_FPGA_Load   : Route C-in  — FPGA出力の .npy を取り込み s_raw として使用\n\n性能: NUFFT本体（~84s on RTX 5080）は旧 n32 と同じ。末尾の IFFT（~1秒）だけ各ルートノードへ移動した。"
          },
          "codeCollapsed": true
        }
      },
