      {
        "id": "n41",
        "type": "canvasNode",
        "position": {
          "x": 2606.207951414265,
          "y": 1986
        },
        "width": 1258,
        "data": {
          "label": "Python Code",
          "category": "processing",
          "blockType": "python_code",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "in_0",
              "label": "in_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "outputs": [
            {
              "id": "out_0",
              "label": "out_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 6 (2-D): top-down view of the focused image [img] in dB. The 3-D surface\n# (n18) shows valleys between azimuth ridges that, seen at an angle, can read as\n# features the image does not actually contain. This flat 2-D imshow is the\n# faithful top-down picture for judging the real focused image.\n#\n# Emits TWO separate PNGs (Full, then Crop). The frontend shows a Full/Crop\n# toggle + Expand for any node that emits multiple images. Display-only:\n# dB-normalised exactly like the 3-D path (20*log10(|img|/max), clipped -40..0),\n# inferno. Full is max-pooled to a display cap (peak-preserving, display only);\n# Crop is the view window at full resolution. The physical img is never modified.\n# Orientation: origin='upper' + y extent (max..min) so azimuth increases\n# DOWNWARD, matching the 3-D plot (n18) and keeping the image upright.\n# Aspect: aspect='equal' so range and azimuth share the same metric scale\n# (1 km in range = 1 km in azimuth on screen). The figure shape is driven by\n# the data extent, not stretched to fill the axes.\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib\nmatplotlib.use('Agg')\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport io, base64\nfrom IPython.display import display\n\ndef _db(a):\n    A = np.abs(a)\n    d = 20.0 * np.log10(A / (A.max() + 1e-12) + 1e-12)\n    return np.clip(d, -40.0, 0.0)\n\ndef _pool_to(a, cap=1200):\n    R, C = a.shape\n    fr = max(1, int(np.ceil(R / cap))); fc = max(1, int(np.ceil(C / cap)))\n    if fr == 1 and fc == 1:\n        return a\n    Rt = (R // fr) * fr; Ct = (C // fc) * fc\n    return a[:Rt, :Ct].reshape(Rt // fr, fr, Ct // fc, fc).max(axis=(1, 3))\n\ndef _emit_png(field_db, x0, x1, y0, y1, title):\n    # Figure size sized to data extent so aspect='equal' fits without huge margins.\n    dx = abs(x1 - x0); dy = abs(y1 - y0)\n    base_h = 4.5  # inches reserved for image height\n    img_w = base_h * (dx / dy) if dy > 0 else base_h\n    img_w = max(3.0, min(12.0, img_w))  # clamp to a sensible range\n    fig_w = img_w + 1.8  # extra room for colorbar + labels\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(fig_w, base_h + 0.6))\n    im = ax.imshow(field_db, origin='upper', cmap='inferno', vmin=-40, vmax=0,\n                   aspect='equal', extent=[x0, x1, y0, y1])\n    ax.set_title(title); ax.set_xlabel('range [m]'); ax.set_ylabel('azimuth [m]')\n    fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax, label='[dB]', shrink=0.85)\n    buf = io.BytesIO(); fig.savefig(buf, format='png', dpi=110, bbox_inches='tight')\n    plt.close(fig)\n    display({'image/png': base64.b64encode(buf.getvalue()).decode('ascii')}, raw=True)\n\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = float(view_scale)\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_ac = np.where((az_pos >= -_W) & (az_pos <= _W))[0]\n_crop = np.abs(img[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1])\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]; _azx = az_pos[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1]\n\n# 1) FULL (max-pooled for display)\nfull_db = _db(_pool_to(np.abs(img)))\n_emit_png(full_db, rg_axis.min(), rg_axis.max(), az_pos.max(), az_pos.min(),\n          'Focused image FULL (2-D, dB)')\n# 2) CROP (view window, full resolution — no pool)\ncrop_db = _db(_crop)\n_emit_png(crop_db, _rgx.min(), _rgx.max(), _azx.max(), _azx.min(),\n          'Focused image CROP (2-D, +/-%dm)' % int(_W))\nprint('2-D focused: full', img.shape, 'pooled', full_db.shape, '| crop', _crop.shape)\n",
            "label": "Plot Focused Image (2-D)"
          },
          "codeCollapsed": true
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "n42",
        "type": "canvasNode",
        "position": {
          "x": 1700,
          "y": 1000
        },
        "width": 400,
        "data": {
          "label": "Python Code",
          "category": "processing",
          "blockType": "python_code",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "in_0",
              "label": "in_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "outputs": [
            {
              "id": "out_0",
              "label": "out_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# === FPGA Route A: Float Ideal (IFFT) ===\n# 浮動小数点理想ルート。S_all と chirp_fft を周波数領域で乗算して IFFT 戻し、\n# raw echo s_raw を生成する。旧 n32 末尾と完全等価（complex64、GPU 1バッチ）。\n#\n# Enable してこのノードを動かすと s_raw が kernel に出て、下流 n25 (LNA) に\n# 流れる。Route B (n32_Fixed) / Route C-in (n32_FPGA_Load) と同時 Enable しない\n# こと（s_raw が衝突する）。Route C-out (n32_FPGA_Save) とは併用可。\nimport numpy as np\nimport cupy as cp\nimport time as _time\n_t0 = _time.monotonic()\n\nS_gpu = cp.asarray(S_all)\nchirp_gpu = cp.asarray(chirp_fft)\ns_raw = cp.asnumpy(cp.fft.ifft(S_gpu * chirp_gpu[None, :], axis=1)).astype(np.complex64)\ndel S_gpu, chirp_gpu\ncp.get_default_memory_pool().free_all_blocks()\n\nprint('Float route: s_raw=%s peak|s|=%.3f  (%.2fs)'\n      % (s_raw.shape, float(np.abs(s_raw).max()), _time.monotonic() - _t0))\n",
            "label": "FPGA Route A: Float Ideal (IFFT)",
            "spec": "【Route A: 浮動小数点理想ルート】\n\nこのノードを Enable にすると S_all × chirp_fft → IFFT を浮動小数点 (complex64) で計算し、理想的な s_raw を生成する。デフォルトで有効。\n\n入力（kernel namespace 経由）:\n  S_all      (Na, Nr) complex64  — n32 (NUFFT共通) が生成\n  chirp_fft  (Nr,)    complex64  — n32 が生成\n\n出力（kernel namespace）:\n  s_raw      (Na, Nr) complex64  — n25 (LNA) が消費\n\n排他関係:\n  Route B (n32_Fixed) / Route C-in (n32_FPGA_Load) と同時 Enable 不可\n  （s_raw が衝突する）。Route C-out (n32_FPGA_Save) とは併用可。"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "n43",
        "type": "canvasNode",
        "position": {
          "x": 2150,
          "y": 1000
        },
        "width": 400,
        "data": {
          "label": "Python Code",
          "category": "processing",
          "blockType": "python_code",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "in_0",
              "label": "in_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "outputs": [
            {
              "id": "out_0",
              "label": "out_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# === FPGA Route B: Fixed-point (Q-format 3-stage) ===\n# FPGA で必然となるビット幅制限が画質にどう効くかを Python で評価するルート。\n# FPGA実装でよくある FFT × 周波数乗算 × IFFT のパイプラインを fxpmath で\n# 量子化しながら模擬する。3ステージ独立 Q-format:\n#   Stage A : 入力時間領域 (FIR taps + chirp)   --> Q_IN_*\n#   Stage B : FFT 後の周波数領域 (乗算結果含む) --> Q_FFT_*\n#   Stage C : IFFT 後の時間領域 (最終 s_raw)    --> Q_OUT_*\n# 各ステージで auto-scale (peak->full-scale*0.95) → fxpmath で量子化 → 復元。\n# 量子化 SNR を per-stage に表示する。\n#\n# 同時 Enable 排他: Route A (n32_Float) / Route C-in (n32_FPGA_Load) と同時に\n# Enable しないこと（s_raw が衝突する）。Route C-out (n32_FPGA_Save) とは併用可。\nimport numpy as np\nfrom fxpmath import Fxp\nimport time as _time\n_t0 = _time.monotonic()\n\n# --- Q-format parameters (このノード code を編集してチューニング) ----------\n# Stage A: 入力時間領域。chirp / FIR taps は概ね O(1) なので Q1.15 で足りる\nQ_IN_W,  Q_IN_F  = 16, 15\n# Stage B: FFT 後周波数領域。N=Nr ≈ 12k で log2(Nr) ≈ 14 のビット成長があり\n# うる。Q_W=18, Q_F=10 で 8bit 整数 + 10bit 小数（dynamic range 256, 分解能 ~0.001）\nQ_FFT_W, Q_FFT_F = 18, 10\n# Stage C: IFFT 後時間領域。最終 IQ。Q1.15 で十分\nQ_OUT_W, Q_OUT_F = 16, 15\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef qz(x, n_word, n_frac, name=''):\n    \"\"\"Quantize complex array to Q(n_word-n_frac).n_frac signed using fxpmath.\n    Auto-scale by peak so |x|_max maps to ~ Q full-scale * 0.95 (5% overflow\n    headroom), quantize real/imag separately, rescale back. Logs SNR.\"\"\"\n    if x.size == 0:\n        return x.astype(np.complex64)\n    peak = float(max(np.abs(x.real).max(), np.abs(x.imag).max()))\n    if peak == 0:\n        return x.astype(np.complex64)\n    full_scale = float(2 ** (n_word - 1 - n_frac))   # Q-format integer-part max\n    s = 0.95 * full_scale / peak                     # scale factor\n    r_q = Fxp(x.real * s, signed=True, n_word=n_word, n_frac=n_frac).get_val() / s\n    i_q = Fxp(x.imag * s, signed=True, n_word=n_word, n_frac=n_frac).get_val() / s\n    err2 = (x.real - r_q) ** 2 + (x.imag - i_q) ** 2\n    sig2 = (np.abs(x) ** 2).mean()\n    snr_db = 10 * np.log10(sig2 / (err2.mean() + 1e-30))\n    print('  qz[%-9s] Q%d.%d  peak=%.3g  SNR=%.1f dB'\n          % (name, n_word - n_frac, n_frac, peak, snr_db))\n    return (r_q + 1j * i_q).astype(np.complex64)\n\nprint('Fixed route start: Q_IN=Q%d.%d  Q_FFT=Q%d.%d  Q_OUT=Q%d.%d' % (\n    Q_IN_W - Q_IN_F, Q_IN_F,\n    Q_FFT_W - Q_FFT_F, Q_FFT_F,\n    Q_OUT_W - Q_OUT_F, Q_OUT_F))\n\n# --- Stage A: 入力時間領域 ------------------------------------------------\nfir_q   = qz(fir_coefficients, Q_IN_W, Q_IN_F, 'fir_in')\nchirp_q = qz(ref_chirp.astype(np.complex64), Q_IN_W, Q_IN_F, 'chirp_in')\n\n# --- Stage B: FFT 後周波数領域 (乗算ステップ含む) -------------------------\nF    = qz(np.fft.fft(fir_q, axis=1), Q_FFT_W, Q_FFT_F, 'fir_fft')\nC    = qz(np.fft.fft(chirp_q),       Q_FFT_W, Q_FFT_F, 'chirp_fft')\nprod = qz(F * C[None, :],            Q_FFT_W, Q_FFT_F, 'prod')\n\n# --- Stage C: IFFT 後時間領域 -------------------------------------------\ns_raw = qz(np.fft.ifft(prod, axis=1), Q_OUT_W, Q_OUT_F, 'out')\n\nprint('Fixed route: s_raw=%s peak|s|=%.3f  (%.2fs)'\n      % (s_raw.shape, float(np.abs(s_raw).max()), _time.monotonic() - _t0))\n",
            "label": "FPGA Route B: Fixed-point (Q-format 3-stage)",
            "spec": "【Route B: 固定小数点評価ルート (fxpmath)】\n\nFPGA で必然となるビット幅制限が SAR 画像品質にどう効くかを Python 側で評価するルート。FPGA でよくある FFT × 周波数乗算 × IFFT のパイプラインを fxpmath で量子化しながら模擬する。\n\n3ステージ独立 Q-format（ノードコード冒頭の定数を編集してチューニング）:\n\nStage A — 入力時間領域:\n  Q_IN_W=16, Q_IN_F=15  (Q1.15, range ~ [-1, 1))\n  対象: fir_coefficients, ref_chirp\n\nStage B — FFT 後周波数領域 + 乗算後:\n  Q_FFT_W=18, Q_FFT_F=10  (8bit整数 + 10bit小数、dynamic range ~256)\n  FFT 長 Nr ≈ 12k で log2(Nr) ≈ 14 のビット成長があるため整数部に余裕を持たせる\n  対象: fft(fir_coefficients), fft(chirp), F × C[None,:]\n\nStage C — IFFT 後時間領域:\n  Q_OUT_W=16, Q_OUT_F=15  (Q1.15)\n  対象: 最終 s_raw\n\n各ステージは auto-scale: peak を Q full-scale × 0.95 にマップして 5% のオーバーフローヘッドルームを確保 → fxpmath で量子化 → 復元。量子化 SNR を per-stage で表示。\n\n入力（kernel namespace）:\n  S_all, chirp_fft, fir_coefficients, ref_chirp, Na, Nr  ← n32 が生成\n\n出力（kernel namespace）:\n  s_raw  ← n25 (LNA) が消費\n\n排他関係:\n  Route A (n32_Float) / Route C-in (n32_FPGA_Load) と同時 Enable 不可。\n  Route C-out (n32_FPGA_Save) とは併用可（量子化結果を .mat 保存も可能）。\n\n参考: workspace-SAR-SIM/TargetSim_old/target_sim_FFT_FPGA_convert2Image2_375M.ipynb の BadAccuracy モード（int16 直接キャスト）の柔軟版。"
          },
          "enabled": false
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "n44",
        "type": "canvasNode",
        "position": {
          "x": 2600,
          "y": 1000
        },
        "width": 400,
        "data": {
          "label": "Python Code",
          "category": "processing",
          "blockType": "python_code",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "in_0",
              "label": "in_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "outputs": [
            {
              "id": "out_0",
              "label": "out_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# === FPGA Route C-out: Save Coefficients (.mat) ===\n# 外部 FPGA / HDL シミュレータ向けのテストベンチ入力を .mat ファイルに保存。\n# Notebook target_sim_FFT_FPGA_convert2Image2_375M.ipynb の\n# `scipy.io.savemat('conv_cal_data.mat', ...)` と互換 (4 配列 + optional golden)。\n#\n# 保存内容:\n#   chirp_replica          (Nr,)    complex64 - n2 が生成したベースバンドチャープ\n#   chirp_replica_extended (Nr,)    complex64 - 同じ (ref_chirp は既に Nr 長なので\n#                                                Notebook 互換のため別名で同梱)\n#   fir_coefficients       (Na, Nr) complex64 - n32 が生成した時間領域FIRタップ\n#                                                (= ifft(S_all, axis=1))\n#   S_all                  (Na, Nr) complex64 - 周波数領域反射係数 (オリジナル)\n#   golden_iq_data         (Na, Nr) complex64 - include_golden=True 時のみ\n#                                                Route A の s_raw を golden として同梱\n#   meta_*                 (scalars)         - Fs, Nr, Na, R0, lam 等\n#\n# このノードは副作用のみ (kernel に s_raw を出さない)。Route A/B/C-in のどれかと\n# 併用すること (Route A 推奨 - golden_iq_data の出処)。\nimport numpy as np\nimport scipy.io\nimport os\nimport time as _time\n_t0 = _time.monotonic()\n\n# save_path は gui_file_picker (n_save_path) から、include_golden は gui_toggle から\n_path = str(globals().get('save_path', '')).strip()\nif not _path:\n    raise ValueError(\"save_path is empty - set it in the file picker block (var_name='save_path')\")\n\n_inc_golden_str = str(globals().get('include_golden', 'true')).strip().lower()\n_inc_golden = _inc_golden_str in ('1', 'true', 'on', 'yes')\n\n_payload = {\n    'chirp_replica':          ref_chirp.astype(np.complex64),\n    'chirp_replica_extended': ref_chirp.astype(np.complex64),  # already Nr-length\n    'fir_coefficients':       fir_coefficients.astype(np.complex64),\n    'S_all':                  S_all.astype(np.complex64),\n    'meta_Fs':                np.float64(Fs),\n    'meta_Nr':                np.int64(Nr),\n    'meta_Na':                np.int64(Na),\n    'meta_R0':                np.float64(R0),\n    'meta_lam':               np.float64(lam),\n    'meta_t_r_center':        np.float64(t_r_center),\n}\n\nif _inc_golden:\n    if 's_raw' in globals():\n        _payload['golden_iq_data'] = s_raw.astype(np.complex64)\n        print('  including golden s_raw (peak|s|=%.3f) from earlier route'\n              % float(np.abs(s_raw).max()))\n    else:\n        print('  include_golden=true but s_raw not in kernel; enable Route A first')\n\n# ensure parent directory exists\n_dir = os.path.dirname(_path)\nif _dir and not os.path.isdir(_dir):\n    os.makedirs(_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nscipy.io.savemat(_path, _payload, do_compression=False)\n_size_mb = os.path.getsize(_path) / 1e6\nprint('Saved FPGA coefficients to %s  (%.1f MB, %d keys, %.2fs)'\n      % (_path, _size_mb, len(_payload), _time.monotonic() - _t0))\n",
            "label": "FPGA Route C-out: Save Coefficients (.mat)",
            "spec": "【Route C-out: FPGA向け係数を .mat に保存】\n\n外部 FPGA / HDL シミュレータ向けのテストベンチ入力を保存する副作用ノード。Notebook target_sim_FFT_FPGA_convert2Image2_375M.ipynb の scipy.io.savemat 部分と互換。\n\n入力（kernel namespace）:\n  ref_chirp        (Nr,)    complex64 ← n2\n  fir_coefficients (Na, Nr) complex64 ← n32 (時間領域FIRタップ、unshifted)\n  S_all            (Na, Nr) complex64 ← n32 (周波数領域反射係数)\n  s_raw            (Na, Nr) complex64 ← Route A/B/C-in（include_golden=True 時に同梱）\n  Fs, Nr, Na, R0, lam, t_r_center (scalars) ← n1/n2\n\nGUI 入力:\n  save_path     (gui_file_picker) — 保存先 .mat パス\n  include_golden (gui_toggle)    — True で Route A 等の s_raw を同梱\n\n出力: なし (副作用のみ)。s_raw は変更しないので、Route A と併用して golden を生成・保存するのが標準ワークフロー。\n\n保存内容（.mat キー）:\n  chirp_replica, chirp_replica_extended, fir_coefficients, S_all\n  golden_iq_data (optional)\n  meta_Fs, meta_Nr, meta_Na, meta_R0, meta_lam, meta_t_r_center\n\n外部 HDL での使い方: MATLAB / Simulink で load() し、testbench 入力として chirp と fir_coefficients を流し込む。golden_iq_data と FPGA 出力 (Route C-in が読む .npy) を比較して量子化誤差・実装誤差を検証。"
          },
          "enabled": false
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "n45",
        "type": "canvasNode",
        "position": {
